    {
      "query": "Our maintenance team needs a replacement section for an E2 series energy chain with a 30mm inner width and a 38mm bending radius. What is the complete top-level igus part number we need to order so the production line isn't delayed by incompatible links?",
      "agent": {
        "text": "To ensure complete compatibility with your existing links and avoid production delays, you must verify whether your current chain opens along the inner or outer radius. \n\nFor an igus E2 series (specifically the modern E2.1 generation) with a 30mm inner width ($Bi$) and a 38mm bending radius ($R$), the exact orderable part numbers are:\n\n*   **E2.15.30.038.0** \u2013 Crossbars snap open along the **outer** radius.\n*   **E2i.15.30.038.0** \u2013 Crossbars snap open along the **inner** radius.\n\n**Part Number Breakdown:**\n*   **E2 / E2i:** E2.1 series (outer-opening vs. inner-opening).\n*   **15:** Series size index (~14.4mm inner height).\n*   **30:** 30mm inner width. \n*   **038:** 38mm bending radius.\n*   **0:** Standard black color.\n\n*Note on Legacy Chains:* If your equipment uses the older, classic \"E2 micro\" non-opening chains, the legacy SKU format is **10.030.038.0**. If it uses the classic \"zipper\" style, the SKU is **15.030.038.0** or **09.30.038.0**. Verify your exact series generation (E2.1 vs. Classic) before ordering to guarantee link-to-link compatibility.",
